WEBVTT

00:00:49.404 --> 00:00:52.073
STILL SHINING

00:01:06.504 --> 00:01:08.339
You two must have looked
inside the test room.

00:01:08.423 --> 00:01:09.549
Did it have a clock?

00:01:09.632 --> 00:01:10.550
It didn't.

00:01:11.342 --> 00:01:13.553
I'm sure they'll tell you the time,
but just in case,

00:01:13.636 --> 00:01:15.847
make sure you two bring watches.

00:01:15.930 --> 00:01:19.309
I'll pick you up at 7:00 a.m. tomorrow,
so come to the bus stop.

00:01:19.392 --> 00:01:21.769
-Don't be late.
-Okay.

00:01:23.188 --> 00:01:24.439
Go to bed early,

00:01:24.522 --> 00:01:27.192
make sure you eat breakfast,
and don't forget your packed lunch.

00:01:27.275 --> 00:01:29.569
And your exam ID slip. That's crucial.

00:01:29.652 --> 00:01:30.653
-Yes, sir.
-Okay.

00:01:31.946 --> 00:01:33.531
-Get a good night's sleep.
-Okay.

00:01:40.038 --> 00:01:40.955
Hello?

00:01:44.250 --> 00:01:46.669
Well, that…

00:01:47.253 --> 00:01:49.047
You mean the paperwork?

00:01:49.964 --> 00:01:52.050
Let's meet at 6:50 a.m. tomorrow.

00:01:52.133 --> 00:01:53.468
If you go in the room…

00:01:54.052 --> 00:01:55.386
The second drawer on the right.

00:01:55.470 --> 00:01:56.846
Okay. Sleep tight.

00:01:57.513 --> 00:01:58.973
It's there? I told you.

00:01:59.057 --> 00:02:00.892
Okay, I got it.

00:02:01.476 --> 00:02:03.228
Okay, bye.

00:02:10.568 --> 00:02:11.861
You didn't have to wait outside.

00:02:11.945 --> 00:02:13.613
Hello, Mr. Mu.

00:02:14.155 --> 00:02:16.157
You've gone above and beyond to help

00:02:16.241 --> 00:02:18.868
right up until the day before the exam.

00:02:18.952 --> 00:02:21.371
-We're really grateful.
-Not at all.

00:02:21.454 --> 00:02:22.747
It's my pleasure.

00:02:24.374 --> 00:02:28.336
Sir, Tae-seo needs a wristwatch,
but mine's digital.

00:02:28.419 --> 00:02:29.587
Do you have an analog one?

00:02:30.838 --> 00:02:33.132
This one's over 40 years old.

00:02:33.216 --> 00:02:34.550
It's fine as long as it works.

00:02:35.927 --> 00:02:36.886
Is that so?

00:02:38.554 --> 00:02:39.681
Give me your hand.

00:02:40.431 --> 00:02:41.391
Put it on now,

00:02:41.474 --> 00:02:42.517
so you don't forget.

00:02:50.858 --> 00:02:53.319
You two did a great job looking after him.

00:02:54.487 --> 00:02:56.114
You did far more for him.

00:03:47.999 --> 00:03:49.042
Did you sleep well?

00:03:49.125 --> 00:03:51.377
Yeah, better than I thought I would.

00:03:51.461 --> 00:03:53.087
I thought I'd be too nervous to sleep.

00:03:53.671 --> 00:03:56.507
I think knowing you'd be taking
the exam in the next room

00:03:56.591 --> 00:03:57.800
made me feel at ease.

00:04:00.887 --> 00:04:03.014
Did you wait long? You must've been cold.

00:04:03.890 --> 00:04:04.849
I'm hot.

00:04:04.932 --> 00:04:07.518
My dad said it's always cold
in Korea on exam day.

00:04:10.271 --> 00:04:11.189
I want to wear it.

00:04:20.907 --> 00:04:21.949
Like this?

00:04:22.033 --> 00:04:22.867
No.

00:04:26.579 --> 00:04:29.415
Wrap it round and around,

00:04:30.833 --> 00:04:31.834
and then tie it.

00:04:42.387 --> 00:04:45.515
My goal is to get into a school
as close to you as possible.

00:04:46.391 --> 00:04:48.935
If I can't get into one in Seoul,
then at least one nearby.

00:04:52.105 --> 00:04:55.191
Please let us both
achieve our goals today.

00:04:57.110 --> 00:04:58.111
I think

00:04:58.820 --> 00:05:00.405
this will help me do well.

00:05:01.572 --> 00:05:02.740
Give me something too.

00:05:02.824 --> 00:05:03.741
Anything of yours.

00:05:13.126 --> 00:05:13.960
I have something.

00:05:16.546 --> 00:05:18.673
YEONWOO HIGH SCHOOL
YEON TAE-SEO

00:05:19.298 --> 00:05:20.133
My lucky charm.

00:05:22.593 --> 00:05:26.139
EXAM ROOM 6

00:05:44.490 --> 00:05:50.413
STILL SHINING

00:05:51.789 --> 00:05:54.458
The exam's over!

00:05:57.712 --> 00:05:58.713
Am I the only happy one?

00:06:02.842 --> 00:06:03.718
It's over!

00:06:07.221 --> 00:06:09.515
Tae-seo, let's go see the Hangang River.

00:06:09.599 --> 00:06:11.392
We've seen the ocean,
so we need to go there.

00:06:12.059 --> 00:06:13.144
But the time…

00:06:13.227 --> 00:06:14.353
Come on. We can make it.

00:06:15.855 --> 00:06:16.898
One second.

00:06:24.947 --> 00:06:26.032
I only have 7,000 won.

00:06:26.574 --> 00:06:27.491
Let's go next time.

00:06:32.288 --> 00:06:34.540
I didn't use my allowance
since I was studying with you.

00:06:34.624 --> 00:06:36.876
You helped me save it,
so I should spend it with you.

00:06:36.959 --> 00:06:38.461
Come on, let's take the train.

00:06:46.469 --> 00:06:47.720
Not the train.

00:06:58.147 --> 00:07:00.274
Let's see the river
from Dongseoul Bus Terminal.

00:07:00.358 --> 00:07:01.567
Can you see it from there?

00:07:01.651 --> 00:07:03.945
Yeah, the Hangang River is close
to Gangbyeon Station.

00:07:05.154 --> 00:07:07.406
We'll see the river,
leave from Gangbyeon Station,

00:07:07.490 --> 00:07:10.660
take the last train from Cheongnyangni,
and arrive early tomorrow morning.

00:07:10.743 --> 00:07:12.119
Why are we taking the train back?

00:07:12.662 --> 00:07:15.498
The train takes around six hours…

00:07:18.167 --> 00:07:21.462
so we can be together for longer.

00:07:23.589 --> 00:07:24.465
Genius.

00:07:27.843 --> 00:07:29.804
What can we do with 7,000 won?

00:07:31.514 --> 00:07:32.932
Buy me noodles from a tent bar.

00:07:33.015 --> 00:07:35.518
My dad said the noodles
in Seoul tent bars are really good.

00:07:36.811 --> 00:07:37.645
Okay.

00:07:49.407 --> 00:07:50.992
-Want to go there?
-Okay.

00:07:52.535 --> 00:07:53.869
Here are your noodles.

00:07:53.953 --> 00:07:55.121
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

00:08:03.588 --> 00:08:05.047
It's familiar, but it's delicious.

00:08:10.094 --> 00:08:11.971
I love noodles.

00:08:12.054 --> 00:08:13.973
And every time, my dad would say

00:08:14.056 --> 00:08:15.600
that when my mom was pregnant with me,

00:08:15.683 --> 00:08:17.226
she'd always crave these noodles.

00:08:17.768 --> 00:08:19.895
I'd always wondered what they tasted like.

00:08:25.568 --> 00:08:26.777
I know.

00:08:26.861 --> 00:08:29.071
I'm always talking
about my mom when I come to Seoul.

00:08:29.155 --> 00:08:30.364
I don't miss her though.

00:08:33.701 --> 00:08:34.535
Does she live here?

00:08:35.828 --> 00:08:36.954
No, she lives abroad.

00:08:37.955 --> 00:08:39.248
But I don't know where.

00:08:39.332 --> 00:08:40.666
I never asked.

00:08:42.335 --> 00:08:44.170
I'm sure she's doing well somewhere.

00:08:45.671 --> 00:08:47.798
Somewhere that has nothing to do with me.

00:08:52.637 --> 00:08:54.680
We can take the subway
at 10:00 p.m., so don't rush.

00:08:55.806 --> 00:08:57.058
What about the Hangang River?

00:08:58.100 --> 00:08:59.685
You can see it from the station.

00:08:59.769 --> 00:09:01.062
Not from the station.

00:09:01.145 --> 00:09:02.938
I want to see it up close.

00:09:07.818 --> 00:09:08.736
We better eat quickly.

00:09:15.910 --> 00:09:17.953
The Hangang River's right in front of me.

00:09:18.037 --> 00:09:19.038
This is my first time.

00:09:19.121 --> 00:09:19.997
Me too.

00:09:20.790 --> 00:09:22.958
-Let's get a bit closer.
-Wait.

00:09:24.919 --> 00:09:25.961
You're…

00:09:26.712 --> 00:09:27.630
going to be cold.

00:09:29.507 --> 00:09:30.424
Wrap it round…

00:09:32.093 --> 00:09:33.094
and around,

00:09:33.678 --> 00:09:34.553
and then tie it.

00:09:38.015 --> 00:09:39.975
What about you? Aren't you cold?

00:09:40.059 --> 00:09:40.893
I can…

00:09:42.812 --> 00:09:43.771
just wear this.

00:09:57.618 --> 00:09:58.661
It's a historic day.

00:09:58.744 --> 00:10:00.705
I saw both the ocean
and the Hangang River.

00:10:01.956 --> 00:10:03.416
I have to remember this day.

00:10:10.548 --> 00:10:11.382
Yeon Tae-seo.

00:10:11.465 --> 00:10:13.509
I just found my dream.

00:10:13.592 --> 00:10:14.552
Living on my own.

00:10:15.177 --> 00:10:16.512
Living away from my dad.

00:10:16.595 --> 00:10:19.098
This counts as a dream

00:10:19.181 --> 00:10:21.600
because it's only possible
if my dad gets better.

00:10:21.684 --> 00:10:24.103
If he's not doing well,
I can't even consider it.

00:10:24.186 --> 00:10:27.565
My dream is for my dad to get well
so I can become independent.

00:10:29.567 --> 00:10:30.401
How about you?

00:10:31.485 --> 00:10:32.486
Me?

00:10:33.237 --> 00:10:34.363
Mine is…

00:10:37.283 --> 00:10:39.493
If yours is independence,
mine is self-reliance.

00:10:40.161 --> 00:10:41.412
I don't have a "from."

00:10:42.830 --> 00:10:44.165
That's really amazing.

00:10:44.915 --> 00:10:45.750
What do you mean?

00:10:45.833 --> 00:10:49.003
Because I know
you'll achieve that like it's nothing.

00:10:49.587 --> 00:10:52.339
From what I've seen,
you're good at doing things on your own.

00:10:53.591 --> 00:10:55.801
-I am?
-Yeah.

00:10:55.885 --> 00:10:57.720
I don't like doing things by myself,

00:10:57.803 --> 00:10:59.263
but you're really good at it.

00:10:59.346 --> 00:11:01.891
I've never seen you hang out with people.

00:11:02.475 --> 00:11:03.768
You're fine on your own.

00:11:04.393 --> 00:11:05.603
It's kind of amazing.

00:11:07.062 --> 00:11:08.189
Then again,

00:11:08.272 --> 00:11:10.566
I bet things will be different
when you go to college.

00:11:12.193 --> 00:11:14.737
I wonder what else will change about you.

00:11:16.781 --> 00:11:18.616
I doubt anything will change.

00:11:23.204 --> 00:11:24.205
Want to go a bit further?

00:11:25.956 --> 00:11:27.833
Yeah. Do we have time?

00:11:31.879 --> 00:11:33.589
No, we don't.

00:11:35.883 --> 00:11:36.717
Let's go.

00:11:37.801 --> 00:11:38.636
We have to go.

00:11:38.719 --> 00:11:40.012
Come on, we'll be late.

00:11:52.107 --> 00:11:53.943
We walked way too far to see the river.

00:11:57.279 --> 00:11:58.280
Hold on.

00:11:59.406 --> 00:12:00.407
Gosh, I'm exhausted.

00:12:00.950 --> 00:12:02.117
I burned off all the noodles.

00:12:05.538 --> 00:12:06.705
Come on, we're late.

00:12:10.334 --> 00:12:11.335
Let's go.

00:12:17.424 --> 00:12:18.425
Run.

00:12:43.367 --> 00:12:46.912
This morning at the bus stop,

00:12:47.454 --> 00:12:48.956
I was watching you arrive.

00:13:07.141 --> 00:13:08.684
Where we'll be,

00:13:09.602 --> 00:13:10.644
what we'll be doing,

00:13:11.437 --> 00:13:12.563
and with whom.

00:13:14.106 --> 00:13:17.985
I wondered which of these three
would be decided by today's exam.

00:13:20.195 --> 00:13:21.030
Then,

00:13:21.822 --> 00:13:25.075
could this be the last time

00:13:25.659 --> 00:13:27.119
we're headed

00:13:28.746 --> 00:13:30.080
in the same direction?

00:13:33.542 --> 00:13:35.169
It's not certain yet,

00:13:36.086 --> 00:13:38.922
but things will change
when we're at different schools, right?

00:13:40.716 --> 00:13:41.759
No.

00:13:42.468 --> 00:13:45.804
Distance only mattered
when text messages didn't exist.

00:13:48.557 --> 00:13:50.643
If we can still send texts,

00:13:51.310 --> 00:13:52.519
no place is too far.

00:13:53.437 --> 00:13:54.813
We can text from anywhere.

00:13:54.897 --> 00:13:56.190
Exactly.

00:13:57.358 --> 00:13:58.734
Texting works everywhere.

00:13:59.360 --> 00:14:00.903
Even Yeonwoo has great service.

00:14:02.154 --> 00:14:05.866
Would texting not work somewhere
really remote in another country?

00:14:05.949 --> 00:14:07.701
Unless we're in different worlds,

00:14:09.286 --> 00:14:10.496
we can still text.

00:14:12.081 --> 00:14:13.248
Different worlds…

00:14:15.376 --> 00:14:16.627
That's my mom and me.

00:14:20.089 --> 00:14:20.964
Same.

00:14:25.177 --> 00:14:27.596
There's something that only applies to us.

00:14:29.306 --> 00:14:30.641
Because it's you and me.

00:14:32.726 --> 00:14:37.606
You and I are going to try really hard
to spend time together.

00:14:39.483 --> 00:14:41.276
We'll make every effort.

00:14:45.781 --> 00:14:47.783
You like me that much?

00:14:49.159 --> 00:14:50.160
Of course.

00:14:50.744 --> 00:14:52.746
If I hadn't been this sure,

00:14:54.790 --> 00:14:56.166
I wouldn't have even tried.

00:14:57.459 --> 00:14:58.502
Even when I had…

00:15:01.005 --> 00:15:04.091
no room in my life to like someone,
these feelings still grew.

00:16:48.570 --> 00:16:49.863
I want to be with you.

00:17:12.344 --> 00:17:13.887
-Shall we?
-Yeah.

00:17:14.388 --> 00:17:15.389
Shall we?

00:18:05.564 --> 00:18:06.690
Where should I go?

00:18:09.610 --> 00:18:10.694
Over there?

00:19:23.100 --> 00:19:24.893
Your room is nice.

00:19:25.811 --> 00:19:26.770
Yeah.

00:19:44.288 --> 00:19:45.122
Let me…

00:19:45.706 --> 00:19:46.707
I can do it.

00:20:58.278 --> 00:20:59.112
Hold on.

00:21:35.107 --> 00:21:36.108
Sorry.

00:22:21.486 --> 00:22:22.571
Eun-a, are you home?

00:22:30.912 --> 00:22:32.080
Is that your dad?

00:22:33.748 --> 00:22:34.833
Eun-a.

00:22:34.916 --> 00:22:36.376
Yeah, Dad!

00:22:42.549 --> 00:22:43.717
I'm home.

00:22:45.218 --> 00:22:46.761
I'm going to wash up and go to bed.

00:22:46.845 --> 00:22:48.346
Are you going to school tomorrow?

00:22:48.430 --> 00:22:49.973
I have to, but I can go late.

00:22:51.558 --> 00:22:52.559
Good night, Dad.

00:22:53.476 --> 00:22:54.853
Okay, well done today.

00:22:55.395 --> 00:22:56.396
Get some rest.

00:22:57.189 --> 00:22:58.398
I'm proud of you, my girl.

00:22:59.232 --> 00:23:00.192
Thanks.

00:23:16.208 --> 00:23:17.167
Is he gone?

00:23:56.164 --> 00:23:57.165
No.

00:24:01.795 --> 00:24:04.381
Actually, I have a huge secret.

00:24:06.383 --> 00:24:08.885
I was too embarrassed to tell you.

00:24:25.110 --> 00:24:26.820
I was so hot I thought I'd die.

00:24:28.029 --> 00:24:30.323
I kept thinking about my thermals
as I took off my coat.

00:24:30.407 --> 00:24:32.993
It wasn't even that cold today,
but my dad insisted.

00:24:35.495 --> 00:24:36.788
This is so embarrassing.

00:24:36.871 --> 00:24:39.124
Why did it have to be floral?

00:24:42.002 --> 00:24:43.086
What?

00:24:44.254 --> 00:24:45.463
I think it's cute.

00:25:36.890 --> 00:25:38.975
You've always done well,

00:25:39.059 --> 00:25:40.602
so let's just figure out where to go.

00:25:40.685 --> 00:25:41.978
Go think about it.

00:25:42.062 --> 00:25:43.730
Okay. Thank you.

00:25:43.813 --> 00:25:44.773
Off you go.

00:25:49.319 --> 00:25:50.445
My gosh.

00:26:09.589 --> 00:26:11.966
Mo Eun-a, well done. You did a good job.

00:26:12.926 --> 00:26:13.760
Thank you.

00:26:14.719 --> 00:26:18.264
You did really well considering
you only started studying half a year ago.

00:26:19.265 --> 00:26:20.100
Really.

00:26:20.600 --> 00:26:22.268
If you'd started a year earlier,

00:26:23.186 --> 00:26:25.105
we could've tried
the regional admissions track.

00:26:25.688 --> 00:26:26.689
It's a shame.

00:26:28.525 --> 00:26:30.068
Now, let's see.

00:27:06.229 --> 00:27:11.985
DECEMBER

00:27:19.659 --> 00:27:21.536
DEPARTMENT OF MECHANICAL ENGINEERING

00:27:21.619 --> 00:27:23.121
YOUR APPLICATION HAS BEEN SUBMITTED

00:27:23.204 --> 00:27:24.414
All done.

00:27:24.497 --> 00:27:26.666
I feel so glad
to have it submitted quickly.

00:27:27.500 --> 00:27:30.253
The results come out on February 4th, so…

00:27:30.336 --> 00:27:32.088
Just kick back and relax.

00:27:43.099 --> 00:27:44.893
Yeah, it's beautiful.

00:28:03.745 --> 00:28:04.787
Eun-a.

00:28:10.084 --> 00:28:12.086
Merry early Christmas.

00:28:25.725 --> 00:28:26.726
The guests are here.

00:28:26.809 --> 00:28:28.478
Yeah, I'm all done.

00:28:30.146 --> 00:28:32.899
Thanks to your help,
I'm officially on the concierge team now.

00:28:32.982 --> 00:28:33.858
Thank you so much.

00:28:34.859 --> 00:28:37.612
I heard you specifically asked
to work with only me.

00:28:38.655 --> 00:28:39.656
Because you're good.

00:28:43.409 --> 00:28:46.329
I think having to deal with
a different person each time

00:28:46.996 --> 00:28:48.665
bothers Seon-gyu a bit.

00:28:48.748 --> 00:28:50.291
He seemed to struggle with it.

00:28:51.334 --> 00:28:52.961
So it's a win-win.

00:28:55.463 --> 00:28:57.215
You haven't had dinner yet, right?

00:28:57.298 --> 00:29:00.760
You eat this one,
and please take the other one to Eun-a.

00:29:02.637 --> 00:29:05.974
Whenever the guests are here,
she never comes out of her room.

00:29:11.437 --> 00:29:13.314
How did you feel when you submitted it?

00:29:13.398 --> 00:29:16.901
Mr. Mu did it for me.
He clicked the "Submit" button too.

00:29:16.985 --> 00:29:18.152
He clicked it for you?

00:29:18.820 --> 00:29:20.613
I didn't ask him to,

00:29:20.697 --> 00:29:22.407
but it was just easier for him to do it.

00:29:24.075 --> 00:29:26.035
I'd be too nervous to click it myself.

00:29:28.663 --> 00:29:31.457
Do adults always have to deal
with stressful things like this?

00:29:32.208 --> 00:29:34.627
Why am I always so nervous and scared?

00:30:09.120 --> 00:30:10.788
MY APPLICATIONS

00:30:18.922 --> 00:30:21.507
If you're done, I'll click it now.
I'm going to submit it.

00:30:21.591 --> 00:30:23.384
Mr. Mu, wait.

00:30:23.468 --> 00:30:26.346
-No, you've done more than enough.
-Please just wait.

00:30:26.429 --> 00:30:28.598
-I can't wait anymore.
-Wait, hold on!

00:30:28.681 --> 00:30:30.266
It's Christmas today.

00:30:30.350 --> 00:30:31.851
Can I just pray one time?

00:30:35.813 --> 00:30:37.065
I should get up to do it.

00:30:38.066 --> 00:30:39.150
It's okay. Just pray.

00:30:39.233 --> 00:30:41.611
-This gave me a bad feeling.
-Go on, just pray.

00:30:45.406 --> 00:30:47.367
Hopefully, we can make it home today.

00:30:49.869 --> 00:30:51.704
Dear Santa,
I really want to go to college.

00:30:51.788 --> 00:30:54.791
JANUARY

00:31:10.598 --> 00:31:12.058
Oh, my god!

00:31:13.142 --> 00:31:14.477
Why are you hiding in the corner?

00:31:15.061 --> 00:31:16.062
It's so dark.

00:31:17.021 --> 00:31:18.690
-You should've turned the lights on.
-No…

00:31:20.358 --> 00:31:21.567
I'm fine.

00:31:27.615 --> 00:31:28.741
Please come over here.

00:31:54.267 --> 00:31:57.020
One thing's for sure.
We always have plenty to eat at our house.

00:31:58.438 --> 00:31:59.605
Enjoy your meal.

00:32:01.774 --> 00:32:03.901
We need the one you just swiped tonight,

00:32:05.445 --> 00:32:06.696
so take any of these instead.

00:32:08.614 --> 00:32:09.615
Okay.

00:32:42.565 --> 00:32:44.025
Happy New Year.

00:33:29.445 --> 00:33:31.614
My first day as a 20-year-old
with Yeon Tae-seo.

00:33:37.286 --> 00:33:38.329
We don't have any glasses.

00:33:58.516 --> 00:33:59.350
It's sweet.

00:34:13.948 --> 00:34:15.074
It's pretty tasty.

00:34:18.744 --> 00:34:19.745
It's not alcohol.

00:34:19.829 --> 00:34:21.205
It is alcohol.

00:34:55.948 --> 00:34:57.200
Let's go.

00:35:29.774 --> 00:35:31.025
Eun-a!

00:35:33.027 --> 00:35:34.028
Be quiet.

00:35:42.119 --> 00:35:47.583
FEBRUARY

00:35:49.085 --> 00:35:51.796
All right, shall we toast?

00:35:53.422 --> 00:35:55.007
Congratulations.

00:35:55.967 --> 00:35:59.845
He made it to Hanguk National University
from this tiny village. Congratulations.

00:35:59.929 --> 00:36:01.973
You're too kind.

00:36:02.056 --> 00:36:04.183
It's all thanks to Mr. Mu here.

00:36:04.267 --> 00:36:06.519
I didn't do much.

00:36:06.602 --> 00:36:08.271
He achieved it all on his own.

00:36:08.354 --> 00:36:10.690
So did Mr. Mo's daughter not get in?

00:36:10.773 --> 00:36:12.149
No, she's still waiting.

00:36:12.233 --> 00:36:14.068
There's a first round of results,

00:36:14.151 --> 00:36:16.654
then a second, and even a third.

00:36:16.737 --> 00:36:18.364
The results come out in batches.

00:36:18.447 --> 00:36:20.491
So it's a little complicated.

00:36:20.574 --> 00:36:22.576
Gosh, you didn't have to.

00:36:22.660 --> 00:36:24.370
Have some of this, Mr. Mu.

00:36:24.453 --> 00:36:25.705
-Congratulations.
-Great job.

00:36:25.788 --> 00:36:27.164
Thank you.

00:36:27.248 --> 00:36:29.041
So, Mr. Mu.

00:36:29.125 --> 00:36:31.460
Explain it properly so I can understand.

00:36:31.544 --> 00:36:34.505
Well, there is
an additional enrollment period,

00:36:34.588 --> 00:36:39.093
and the results don't finish
coming out until late February.

00:36:39.176 --> 00:36:41.053
What on earth does that mean?

00:36:41.137 --> 00:36:43.889
It must be killing Eun-a
to wait for the results.

00:36:45.266 --> 00:36:46.142
Right.

00:36:52.606 --> 00:36:53.733
This is my first time.

00:36:54.650 --> 00:36:55.651
On the Sea Train?

00:36:56.819 --> 00:36:57.903
THIS IS THE SEA TRAIN

00:36:57.987 --> 00:37:01.490
It only runs during the day
and follows the coastline.

00:37:01.574 --> 00:37:04.577
It takes an hour and 40 minutes
from Gangneung to Samcheok,

00:37:04.660 --> 00:37:06.245
so if we go there and come back…

00:37:06.329 --> 00:37:08.998
We can be together
for around three and a half hours.

00:37:09.749 --> 00:37:10.750
Yeah.

00:37:14.462 --> 00:37:15.838
When I was little,

00:37:16.797 --> 00:37:18.883
my mom worked here for a bit.

00:37:20.134 --> 00:37:22.386
I wanted to become
a Sea Train driver back then.

00:37:23.596 --> 00:37:25.389
I guess it looked kind of cool.

00:37:28.601 --> 00:37:29.935
That's nice.

00:37:32.480 --> 00:37:34.523
What did you want to tell me
all the way out here?

00:37:41.697 --> 00:37:43.908
I have to go to Seoul soon.

00:37:45.576 --> 00:37:48.746
When I was living in Seoul,
I had a friend called Hyeong-seok.

00:37:48.829 --> 00:37:50.498
And his dad runs a study center.

00:37:51.749 --> 00:37:54.752
He let me use it for free
and helped me out a lot.

00:37:56.128 --> 00:37:58.506
He asked if I could do
some tutoring starting in February.

00:37:59.423 --> 00:38:00.925
I'd been putting it off,

00:38:02.009 --> 00:38:04.345
but I think I really have to go now.

00:38:08.849 --> 00:38:10.017
Right.

00:38:12.103 --> 00:38:12.937
You should go.

00:38:14.397 --> 00:38:15.648
And your entrance ceremony?

00:38:15.731 --> 00:38:17.191
Is Hui-seo joining you later?

00:38:17.775 --> 00:38:19.151
He can't go.

00:38:19.235 --> 00:38:20.945
He can't do long journeys yet.

00:38:21.487 --> 00:38:22.696
He must be upset.

00:38:24.281 --> 00:38:25.408
Do you have a place to stay?

00:38:25.491 --> 00:38:28.035
Yeah, the study center office has a bed.

00:38:28.119 --> 00:38:30.162
How can you sleep in an office?

00:38:32.373 --> 00:38:33.457
That's so sad.

00:38:35.209 --> 00:38:36.460
That's nothing.

00:38:38.129 --> 00:38:40.047
You must be more sad
waiting for your results.

00:38:42.800 --> 00:38:43.676
Me? Well…

00:38:44.343 --> 00:38:46.429
One of the three schools I applied to

00:38:47.012 --> 00:38:48.806
is at least close to you,

00:38:49.515 --> 00:38:51.559
but my chances of getting in are low.

00:38:51.642 --> 00:38:54.311
One is halfway between
here and Seoul, but it's not certain.

00:38:54.395 --> 00:38:56.647
The last one is in Gangneung.

00:38:58.065 --> 00:39:01.152
Mr. Mu said it's a good school,
and the program is good there.

00:39:02.361 --> 00:39:03.237
But…

00:39:04.447 --> 00:39:06.157
it's really far from you.

00:39:06.782 --> 00:39:10.953
Having to wait for over a month
is making me anxious and uncertain.

00:39:11.579 --> 00:39:13.414
It's been dragging on for so long

00:39:13.497 --> 00:39:15.458
that I can't believe
February is already ending.

00:39:16.000 --> 00:39:17.209
It feels endless.

00:39:26.635 --> 00:39:28.137
It's definitely going to end.

00:39:30.347 --> 00:39:32.057
I hope so.

00:39:40.441 --> 00:39:42.610
An end that really feels like one.

00:39:43.736 --> 00:39:45.821
I hope it's a clean end.

00:40:12.097 --> 00:40:13.057
Wait.

00:40:17.394 --> 00:40:19.522
This isn't much, but take it.

00:40:19.605 --> 00:40:21.106
I'm fine. I have money.

00:40:21.190 --> 00:40:22.900
Buy yourself something to wear.

00:40:24.568 --> 00:40:26.237
Your grandma seemed to feel bad

00:40:26.320 --> 00:40:28.989
we couldn't buy you something to wear

00:40:29.073 --> 00:40:31.158
to your entrance ceremony.

00:40:32.409 --> 00:40:34.495
We can't afford to buy you a suit,

00:40:34.578 --> 00:40:37.998
but at least buy yourself a coat.

00:40:38.082 --> 00:40:39.833
Something that's nice and formal.

00:40:40.584 --> 00:40:42.962
You'll need to dress up
quite often while in the city.

00:40:43.045 --> 00:40:45.172
Here. Buy one for yourself.

00:40:46.465 --> 00:40:47.633
Thank you.

00:40:49.927 --> 00:40:53.180
From scholarships to tutoring,
you're doing everything on your own.

00:40:53.264 --> 00:40:54.765
We feel terrible.

00:40:58.185 --> 00:40:59.103
I'll visit often.

00:41:00.437 --> 00:41:03.315
There's no need. You should be studying.
You'll only waste money.

00:41:04.692 --> 00:41:06.360
Just make sure you call Hui-seo.

00:41:09.446 --> 00:41:12.241
I thought he'd be grumpy
about missing your entrance ceremony,

00:41:12.950 --> 00:41:13.993
but he's been quiet.

00:41:18.789 --> 00:41:22.626
At least the ceremony doesn't fall
on the same day as your parents' memorial.

00:41:23.836 --> 00:41:25.212
It's the first one.

00:41:32.636 --> 00:41:34.430
I'll go pay my respects.

00:41:35.389 --> 00:41:36.724
Stay at home with Hui-seo.

00:41:41.895 --> 00:41:42.855
All right.

00:41:43.772 --> 00:41:45.065
Go on, then.

00:41:45.983 --> 00:41:46.817
Okay.

00:41:53.490 --> 00:41:59.288
WAITING AREA (TICKETS)

00:42:02.541 --> 00:42:05.377
Are you taking the express bus to Seoul?

00:42:06.795 --> 00:42:07.630
Eun-a.

00:42:10.841 --> 00:42:13.427
I was waiting right here.

00:42:13.510 --> 00:42:15.512
I thought you'd be taking the train.

00:42:15.596 --> 00:42:16.555
I'm such a klutz.

00:42:18.265 --> 00:42:19.475
I just…

00:42:19.558 --> 00:42:22.561
I know you told me not to,
but I'd feel bad if I didn't see you off.

00:42:22.645 --> 00:42:25.814
I'll take you there.
I bought two tickets, so we can just go.

00:42:25.898 --> 00:42:27.024
Don't be ridiculous.

00:42:40.663 --> 00:42:42.915
How can you make me let you go home alone?

00:42:43.791 --> 00:42:44.958
You can let it happen today.

00:42:51.507 --> 00:42:52.925
Seriously, it's fine.

00:42:56.220 --> 00:42:57.638
Let's get off at the next stop.

00:42:58.639 --> 00:43:01.725
I can't bear to watch you go back alone.
I'll take you home and…

00:43:01.809 --> 00:43:03.352
So you can go alone, but I can't?

00:43:05.020 --> 00:43:06.855
That's nonsense. It's fine.

00:43:10.067 --> 00:43:11.735
It's already been an hour.

00:43:11.819 --> 00:43:13.237
We don't have time.

00:43:13.320 --> 00:43:15.072
How long are you going to keep this up?

00:43:25.874 --> 00:43:28.168
LOG IN

00:43:31.213 --> 00:43:33.382
PLAYLIST

00:43:35.843 --> 00:43:36.760
This is my account.

00:43:37.678 --> 00:43:41.682
If I'm using it, it'll say,
"Currently streaming."

00:43:42.433 --> 00:43:44.852
We can use it together.
We'll listen to it at the same time.

00:43:45.519 --> 00:43:46.520
Then,

00:43:47.563 --> 00:43:49.815
it'll feel like we're together.

00:43:51.942 --> 00:43:53.819
It'll feel like we're together.

00:43:53.902 --> 00:43:54.987
Feeling like we're together

00:43:56.363 --> 00:43:57.531
counts as being together.

00:44:01.410 --> 00:44:02.411
I like that.

00:44:03.078 --> 00:44:04.538
What else is there

00:44:04.621 --> 00:44:06.206
to make us feel together?

00:44:07.916 --> 00:44:10.586
Sharing the photos we take?
Let's take one now.

00:44:14.173 --> 00:44:15.007
Smile.

00:44:22.931 --> 00:44:25.267
Sir, how long will it take?

00:44:25.350 --> 00:44:26.268
One hour.

00:44:26.351 --> 00:44:27.186
What?

00:44:31.064 --> 00:44:33.650
You should go.
Let's part here. It's your first lesson.

00:44:34.568 --> 00:44:35.527
Eun-a.

00:44:38.489 --> 00:44:40.240
This is a lot

00:44:40.824 --> 00:44:42.201
harder than I expected.

00:44:43.285 --> 00:44:44.536
I can't do it.

00:44:45.412 --> 00:44:46.497
I can.

00:44:46.580 --> 00:44:49.541
Come on, I can't let you go back alone.

00:44:51.001 --> 00:44:53.212
You can. Just like this.

00:44:53.295 --> 00:44:56.840
I might end up at a college near you,
or I might not.

00:44:57.549 --> 00:44:59.092
I don't know what will happen.

00:45:00.886 --> 00:45:02.137
My life is always so uncertain.

00:45:03.889 --> 00:45:05.766
Anyway, we'll have to keep doing this,

00:45:05.849 --> 00:45:08.352
but if you feel bad or guilty,
it'll be hard to see each other.

00:45:12.898 --> 00:45:13.899
This is driving me crazy.

00:45:17.069 --> 00:45:18.153
I'll…

00:45:18.820 --> 00:45:20.155
I'll do my best for us.

00:45:20.989 --> 00:45:21.907
Okay.

00:45:28.872 --> 00:45:29.748
Oh, my god.

00:45:30.874 --> 00:45:31.875
What?

00:45:31.959 --> 00:45:33.460
What is it?

00:45:33.544 --> 00:45:34.586
I got in.

00:45:35.212 --> 00:45:36.046
What?

00:45:36.630 --> 00:45:38.340
GANGNEUNG WONKYEONG UNIVERSITY

00:45:39.466 --> 00:45:41.218
No way! I got in!

00:45:41.301 --> 00:45:43.720
See? I got in because I was with you!

00:45:44.930 --> 00:45:47.182
Oh, my god. But it's a bit far from you.

00:45:47.266 --> 00:45:49.560
That's not what matters right now!

00:45:50.727 --> 00:45:52.521
Congratulations!

00:45:54.273 --> 00:45:57.693
-You really earned this.
-Oh, my god. I'm so happy.

00:45:57.776 --> 00:46:01.822
MARCH

00:46:47.701 --> 00:46:49.494
-It's nice.
-Nice and clean.

00:46:49.578 --> 00:46:50.912
You must be his roommate.

00:46:50.996 --> 00:46:52.539
I hope you two get along well.

00:46:53.248 --> 00:46:56.376
-The bed here's so soft.
-Sweetie, don't sit there.

00:46:56.460 --> 00:46:58.462
Why not? Come try it too, Mom.

00:47:02.007 --> 00:47:03.091
This is nice.

00:47:15.854 --> 00:47:16.938
Hui-seo…

00:47:19.274 --> 00:47:21.443
I'll bring him over when he's a bit older.

00:47:29.242 --> 00:47:31.036
Don't worry about him.

00:47:34.748 --> 00:47:37.209
And don't worry about Grandma and Grandpa.

00:47:42.089 --> 00:47:43.882
I'll take care of everyone.

00:47:50.764 --> 00:47:51.765
I almost forgot.

00:47:54.017 --> 00:47:56.395
I'm attending the college
you wanted me to go to, Mom.

00:48:03.735 --> 00:48:05.821
You would've been so happy
to see me there.

00:48:13.829 --> 00:48:14.830
Mom.

00:48:17.499 --> 00:48:18.375
Dad.

00:48:59.082 --> 00:49:00.876
Can I sit here?

00:49:00.959 --> 00:49:01.918
Sure.

00:49:12.637 --> 00:49:13.764
I'm Park Na-ri.

00:49:15.390 --> 00:49:16.308
I'm Mo Eun-a.

00:49:18.310 --> 00:49:20.812
Hey, your student number
is right after mine.

00:49:21.521 --> 00:49:22.522
What a coincidence.

00:49:24.775 --> 00:49:26.777
I'm from Seoul. You?

00:49:26.860 --> 00:49:29.070
I live nearby. Twenty minutes by bus.

00:49:29.154 --> 00:49:30.322
-Twenty minutes?
-Yeah.

00:49:36.536 --> 00:49:38.205
No way! We have the same elective too?

00:49:38.288 --> 00:49:40.457
No way! Come sit here.

00:49:47.923 --> 00:49:48.840
What's that?

00:49:52.803 --> 00:49:55.514
-Want to pick one?
-They're so cute.

00:49:56.723 --> 00:49:57.974
-This one.
-Sure.

00:49:58.058 --> 00:49:59.768
-Here.
-Thanks.

00:50:01.019 --> 00:50:05.690
This class is called
Creative Engineering Design.

00:50:05.774 --> 00:50:07.400
This class will give you the opportunity

00:50:07.484 --> 00:50:10.987
to reflect on what lies
beyond the machines.

00:50:11.071 --> 00:50:13.031
Great machines are made
when you understand

00:50:13.114 --> 00:50:14.366
both their function and value.

00:50:14.449 --> 00:50:18.078
What you need for this class
is your mathematical ability

00:50:18.161 --> 00:50:19.913
and a brain that's capable of thinking.

00:50:19.996 --> 00:50:22.958
The rest you will learn
in this class today.

00:50:24.167 --> 00:50:26.419
Did you always want to study
early childhood education?

00:50:26.503 --> 00:50:28.797
Yeah, because I like kids.

00:50:30.298 --> 00:50:33.760
But teaching's not really for me.
It's not what I expected.

00:50:35.637 --> 00:50:38.598
I picked this place for the major,
but now, I'm not so sure.

00:50:41.601 --> 00:50:43.645
But it's so nice to see the ocean.

00:50:44.980 --> 00:50:46.857
This was worth skipping class.

00:50:46.940 --> 00:50:47.774
I know.

00:50:49.860 --> 00:50:51.903
I heard the vending machine coffee
was good here.

00:50:51.987 --> 00:50:54.364
SORI MARKET

00:50:54.447 --> 00:50:55.490
-Want to go?
-Let's go.

00:50:58.493 --> 00:50:59.870
We're already really close.

00:50:59.953 --> 00:51:01.496
I'm exploring Gangneung thanks to her.

00:51:01.580 --> 00:51:03.582
I'll take you around
the next time you're here.

00:51:03.665 --> 00:51:05.000
Okay.

00:51:07.419 --> 00:51:09.629
I have matching stickers with Na-ri,

00:51:09.713 --> 00:51:11.840
but I don't have
anything matching with you.

00:51:14.718 --> 00:51:15.969
What do you want to do?

00:51:17.762 --> 00:51:19.514
I have a great idea.

00:51:19.598 --> 00:51:22.017
What if I make stickers with my drawings?

00:51:22.100 --> 00:51:24.311
The same vegetable stickers
for our different classes.

00:51:24.895 --> 00:51:25.937
Tell me your classes.

00:51:26.021 --> 00:51:27.689
I'll draw something for each one.

00:51:27.772 --> 00:51:28.690
I'm really good.

00:51:30.442 --> 00:51:31.651
Engineering Mathematics.

00:51:32.402 --> 00:51:33.236
Kidney beans.

00:51:33.320 --> 00:51:34.905
It's extremely hard to pick them out.

00:51:36.656 --> 00:51:39.868
They're hard to pick out? Then…

00:51:39.951 --> 00:51:41.077
APRIL

00:51:43.705 --> 00:51:45.290
-Kim Na-rae.
-Here.

00:51:47.167 --> 00:51:48.335
Kim Ji-ho.

00:51:49.836 --> 00:51:50.795
Ji-ho?

00:51:52.339 --> 00:51:54.090
-Mo Eun-a.
-Here.

00:51:55.717 --> 00:51:56.718
Park Na-ri.

00:51:57.844 --> 00:51:59.429
Right, Na-ri took a leave of absence.

00:52:00.597 --> 00:52:04.184
It's only been a month,
and someone's already taking time off.

00:52:06.227 --> 00:52:08.313
-Park Seo-yeon.
-Here.

00:52:08.396 --> 00:52:10.398
-Song A-yeong.
-Here.

00:52:21.409 --> 00:52:22.577
PLAYLIST

00:52:31.628 --> 00:52:33.630
TAE-SEO

00:52:33.713 --> 00:52:35.757
Have the flowers bloomed in Seoul yet?

00:52:35.840 --> 00:52:37.342
It's crazy here.

00:52:37.425 --> 00:52:39.552
Send me a photo
of the flowers at your school too.

00:52:39.636 --> 00:52:43.223
And a selfie of you in front of them too.

00:52:47.394 --> 00:52:49.729
I miss you, Tae-seo.

00:52:50.897 --> 00:52:52.941
-Hello.
-Hello.

00:53:05.870 --> 00:53:08.498
I'll go to school after tutoring
and send it to you.

00:53:23.263 --> 00:53:26.599
His tutoring session usually takes
about two hours, so…

00:53:28.518 --> 00:53:30.729
Call me when you're done tutoring, okay?

00:53:49.414 --> 00:53:50.999
What time do you finish?

00:53:51.875 --> 00:53:53.668
WHAT TIME DO YOU FINISH?

00:54:02.093 --> 00:54:03.928
I have two tutoring sessions today,

00:54:04.012 --> 00:54:05.722
so if I go straight to school after,

00:54:05.805 --> 00:54:07.015
it should be around 10:00 p.m.

00:54:16.816 --> 00:54:18.526
One ticket to Gangneung, please.

00:54:19.277 --> 00:54:20.403
Gangneung?

00:54:21.112 --> 00:54:22.322
That'll be 10,600 won.

00:54:26.910 --> 00:54:27.744
Dad.

00:54:29.871 --> 00:54:31.164
You never ask me to pick you up.

00:54:31.915 --> 00:54:32.957
I didn't want to go alone.

00:54:33.958 --> 00:54:35.919
Are we going out for a night stroll?

00:54:36.002 --> 00:54:38.129
Where should we go? Let's go for sashimi.

00:54:40.090 --> 00:54:41.132
I'm tired.

00:54:55.814 --> 00:54:57.607
What should we eat?

00:54:57.690 --> 00:54:59.692
Is there something you'd like to eat?

00:55:00.610 --> 00:55:01.986
I'm up for anything.

00:55:03.238 --> 00:55:04.280
Should we ask Eun-a?

00:55:04.364 --> 00:55:06.491
Eun-a, is there anything you want to eat?

00:55:07.700 --> 00:55:08.868
Eun-a, are you asleep?

00:55:10.703 --> 00:55:12.122
She must be really tired.

00:55:12.205 --> 00:55:13.790
Just let her sleep.

00:55:15.208 --> 00:55:16.960
But we haven't gone out
together in forever.

00:55:17.585 --> 00:55:19.546
It'd be nice if we could talk while we go.

00:55:19.629 --> 00:55:21.256
I had no idea they'd bloomed so much.

00:55:22.715 --> 00:55:23.716
Should I call you?

00:55:24.300 --> 00:55:25.426
Is everything okay?

00:55:26.761 --> 00:55:29.305
I was just wandering and thought of you.

00:55:30.890 --> 00:55:33.893
I can leave in the morning this weekend.

00:55:33.977 --> 00:55:34.936
Let's meet up early.

00:55:35.895 --> 00:55:37.313
I want to go to Seoul.

00:55:38.273 --> 00:55:39.566
It's my turn to go.

00:55:39.649 --> 00:55:40.900
I'll come to you.

00:55:40.984 --> 00:55:42.485
No, I'll go to you.

00:55:43.027 --> 00:55:44.445
Spend your time on yourself.

00:55:44.529 --> 00:55:45.864
Don't waste it.

00:55:45.947 --> 00:55:47.574
Hello, Hyeong-seok? Yeah.

00:55:48.241 --> 00:55:50.034
Your time is precious too.

00:55:50.118 --> 00:55:51.077
I'll go to you.

00:55:55.748 --> 00:55:58.001
My time right now is just passing by,

00:55:58.877 --> 00:56:02.213
but yours is time you need to use
toward your goals.

00:56:02.297 --> 00:56:03.423
They're different.

00:56:05.717 --> 00:56:07.385
No more dark photos.

00:56:08.428 --> 00:56:10.180
I miss you, Tae-seo.

00:56:11.347 --> 00:56:12.390
A lot.

00:57:08.112 --> 00:57:09.072
This is nice.

00:57:09.155 --> 00:57:10.365
Did you miss me?

00:57:12.367 --> 00:57:13.201
Of course.

00:57:16.496 --> 00:57:23.461
MAY

00:57:39.310 --> 00:57:41.688
Every time I take out a cigarette,
you appear.

00:57:41.771 --> 00:57:42.814
It's almost scary.

00:57:46.901 --> 00:57:48.695
It's fun working at a hotel, isn't it?

00:57:49.445 --> 00:57:51.489
I feel good
whenever I see the hotel staff.

00:57:51.573 --> 00:57:52.949
Then, try it out.

00:57:53.449 --> 00:57:55.743
A lot of local young people
work part-time at our hotel.

00:57:55.827 --> 00:57:57.078
Taking time off from school?

00:57:58.454 --> 00:57:59.914
What would I be taking time off for?

00:57:59.998 --> 00:58:01.791
I don't want to try things out
without a goal

00:58:01.874 --> 00:58:03.793
just because everyone else is.

00:58:04.919 --> 00:58:05.878
So annoying.

00:58:07.714 --> 00:58:09.966
I mean, I know you're in college,

00:58:10.049 --> 00:58:12.427
but it's not even vacation time
and you're not at school.

00:58:12.510 --> 00:58:15.430
You've been here all day today
and riding your bike the past two days.

00:58:16.180 --> 00:58:17.307
You're the first one to ask.

00:58:17.890 --> 00:58:19.892
I skipped school all week and slacked off,

00:58:19.976 --> 00:58:21.060
but no one's ever asked.

00:58:21.144 --> 00:58:22.937
No one from school reached out.

00:58:23.021 --> 00:58:25.231
And my dad didn't ask why I wasn't going.

00:58:26.065 --> 00:58:27.567
I guess no one really cares.

00:58:28.151 --> 00:58:29.736
Thanks for asking.

00:58:30.278 --> 00:58:32.780
I'm not going to school
because I don't feel like going.

00:58:32.864 --> 00:58:34.782
If you're going to
do college half-heartedly,

00:58:34.866 --> 00:58:37.285
you might as well take time off
and try something else.

00:58:37.368 --> 00:58:38.745
Don't you want to be independent?

00:58:39.370 --> 00:58:40.913
In your current situation,

00:58:40.997 --> 00:58:43.249
I doubt your dad would notice
you're not going to school.

00:58:43.333 --> 00:58:45.460
If I were you,
I'd be thinking about moving out.

00:58:49.464 --> 00:58:51.799
That came out of nowhere. What situation?

00:58:51.883 --> 00:58:53.801
Just go pick up your guests.

00:58:53.885 --> 00:58:56.971
It was a lunch reservation,
but it'll be dinner time soon.

00:58:58.139 --> 00:59:00.642
So-hyeon made
a surprise announcement today.

00:59:00.725 --> 00:59:02.727
I can't really ruin the mood.

00:59:03.394 --> 00:59:04.687
Announcement?

00:59:05.688 --> 00:59:08.399
-You two look great together.
-I'm so happy for you.

00:59:08.483 --> 00:59:09.776
Congratulations.

00:59:09.859 --> 00:59:11.235
-Congratulations.
-Congratulations.

00:59:11.319 --> 00:59:12.236
Congratulations.

00:59:12.320 --> 00:59:14.238
-I'll bring out some more wine.
-All right.

00:59:17.075 --> 00:59:18.159
Cheers.

00:59:25.208 --> 00:59:26.501
You're here just in time.

00:59:26.584 --> 00:59:28.419
Your dad announced
they're getting married.

00:59:28.503 --> 00:59:29.754
You should congratulate them.

00:59:53.319 --> 00:59:54.529
What about the Unit 610 guy?

00:59:55.738 --> 00:59:56.989
It took you long enough to ask.

00:59:58.116 --> 00:59:59.367
I'll end things with him.

00:59:59.450 --> 01:00:00.868
You're only ending it now?

01:00:02.036 --> 01:00:03.913
Seon-gyu knows everything.

01:00:04.831 --> 01:00:07.208
He said he'd tell me
once he figured things out,

01:00:07.291 --> 01:00:09.001
so I hadn't been able to end things.

01:00:11.170 --> 01:00:12.004
Eun-a.

01:00:12.088 --> 01:00:16.759
Love doesn't happen in perfect order.

01:00:16.843 --> 01:00:19.011
No wonder why
you always have a guy around.

01:00:19.095 --> 01:00:20.430
There's never a break with you.

01:00:20.513 --> 01:00:22.473
-Watch what you say.
-You watch it.

01:00:22.557 --> 01:00:24.058
How dare you two-time my dad?

01:00:28.438 --> 01:00:30.106
Seon-gyu is the one I have feelings for.

01:00:30.189 --> 01:00:31.733
The one in Unit 610 knows that too.

01:00:31.816 --> 01:00:34.444
I've never deceived or misled anyone.

01:00:34.527 --> 01:00:36.821
So you're saying you'll live
however you want

01:00:36.904 --> 01:00:38.823
and everyone else
has to just deal with it?

01:00:40.032 --> 01:00:42.160
And my dad just accepted that nonsense?

01:00:44.787 --> 01:00:46.289
What do you take my dad for?

01:00:47.331 --> 01:00:49.917
He's a good person, but someone like you…

01:00:50.001 --> 01:00:50.918
This is the last time.

01:00:51.002 --> 01:00:52.920
I'll let your insults slide today,

01:00:53.004 --> 01:00:54.255
but after this,

01:00:55.047 --> 01:00:56.215
not a chance.

01:01:01.554 --> 01:01:02.388
Mo Eun-a.

01:01:05.349 --> 01:01:06.392
Mo Eun-a!

01:01:07.310 --> 01:01:08.144
Let go.

01:01:09.061 --> 01:01:10.354
You should congratulate them.

01:01:10.438 --> 01:01:12.190
You're startling our guests.

01:01:12.273 --> 01:01:13.733
Take this and go back inside.

01:01:13.816 --> 01:01:15.568
You're so damn good at your job.

01:01:19.864 --> 01:01:23.242
Aren't you a little old to be so worked up
over your dad's relationship?

01:01:24.410 --> 01:01:26.120
You should focus on your own life.

01:01:27.789 --> 01:01:28.956
I'll try to find you a job.

01:01:31.834 --> 01:01:33.211
I can't promise it'll help though.

01:02:31.018 --> 01:02:33.771
It tends to stop or flip over
on steep inclines.

01:02:34.689 --> 01:02:36.566
Could the weight distribution be off?

01:02:36.649 --> 01:02:38.484
How about switching to a two-wheel design?

01:02:38.568 --> 01:02:39.986
Are you busy?

01:02:40.069 --> 01:02:41.279
I'm in my professor's lab.

01:02:41.362 --> 01:02:43.239
It's only for grad students,

01:02:43.322 --> 01:02:45.616
but the TA let me in,
so it's my first time here.

01:02:45.700 --> 01:02:46.659
It's pretty cool.

01:02:47.243 --> 01:02:50.037
You sound busy. What time do you finish?

01:02:50.121 --> 01:02:53.708
What is it? If it's urgent,
I can call you right now.

01:02:53.791 --> 01:02:56.043
You should be majoring in flattery.

01:02:57.044 --> 01:02:59.338
Honestly. We'll continue this in a bit.

01:02:59.422 --> 01:03:01.841
-Never mind. I'll catch you later.
-Yes, Professor.

01:03:02.592 --> 01:03:05.011
The professor likes supreme pizza.

01:03:05.094 --> 01:03:07.305
-Could I go use the restroom?
-Yeah, sure.

01:03:08.639 --> 01:03:09.932
Professor, please have some.

01:03:14.145 --> 01:03:15.605
Did you know?

01:03:16.105 --> 01:03:19.567
Apparently, you can see Namsan
from anywhere in Seoul.

01:03:19.650 --> 01:03:22.987
So from now on, your name is Namsan.

01:03:23.070 --> 01:03:24.280
Yeon Namsan.

01:03:26.741 --> 01:03:30.036
I guess I'm still stuck in uncertainty.

01:03:38.628 --> 01:03:39.712
Where are you?

01:03:40.796 --> 01:03:42.173
The wetlands.

01:03:42.256 --> 01:03:45.384
No. I'm actually at the bus stop now.

01:03:49.055 --> 01:03:51.891
TAE-SEO

01:03:58.397 --> 01:03:59.357
You're in Seoul, right?

01:04:00.983 --> 01:04:03.277
While I was wandering,
I was going to buy some makeup

01:04:03.361 --> 01:04:05.571
and get a bowl of noodles.

01:04:06.280 --> 01:04:08.157
You have important things going on.

01:04:08.240 --> 01:04:09.659
Don't waste your time.

01:04:09.742 --> 01:04:12.745
I have plenty of time,
so I'll drop by again.

01:04:13.663 --> 01:04:15.414
Don't be ridiculous.

01:04:15.498 --> 01:04:17.416
Nothing matters more
than us being together.

01:04:24.215 --> 01:04:27.551
Tae-seo, I really want to see you.

01:04:34.392 --> 01:04:35.351
I'm on my way.

01:04:36.185 --> 01:04:37.520
You don't know where I am.

01:04:38.896 --> 01:04:39.730
Hang on.

01:04:47.905 --> 01:04:49.073
I have one more stop.

01:04:49.156 --> 01:04:49.991
I'm almost there.

01:05:01.961 --> 01:05:03.421
GANGBYEON STATION

01:05:13.764 --> 01:05:16.934
I can hear Yeon Tae-seo coming.

01:05:27.611 --> 01:05:29.405
I'm done wandering.

01:05:32.408 --> 01:05:35.327
STILL SHINING

01:06:01.270 --> 01:06:04.190
You were really going through it
before you did your military duty.

01:06:04.899 --> 01:06:06.442
I hate goodbyes.

01:06:07.359 --> 01:06:08.861
For 10 years, I'd forgotten.

01:06:10.071 --> 01:06:11.405
They were gone.

01:06:11.489 --> 01:06:13.199
Eun-a…

01:06:13.282 --> 01:06:15.159
You haven't heard from her, have you?

01:06:15.868 --> 01:06:17.078
Let's stop…

01:06:18.370 --> 01:06:20.164
with the worries and everything else.

01:06:20.247 --> 01:06:21.457
I thought of you.

01:06:24.668 --> 01:06:27.379
I had hoped to see you at least once.

01:06:34.428 --> 01:06:36.430
Subtitle translation by: Hyesoo Lee